(18, 23, 9, 'Lalbag Fort, Dhaka', '1624465143_lalbag.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lalbag Fort, Dhaka&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lalbagh Fort is located in the Lalbagh area of ​​old Dhaka on the banks of the river Buriganga in the southwest of the capital Dhaka. Although Emperor Aurangzeb planned to build Lalbagh Fort, his son Prince Azam started the construction of Lalbagh Fort in 16 AD. Initially, Lalbagh Fort was named as Aurangabad Fort or Aurangabad Fort. Later, after the death of Iran Dukhat Paribibi, daughter of Subedar Shaista Khan, in 164 AD, he stopped the construction of the fort. In 1844, the Aurangabad area was renamed Lalbagh. Along with the name of the area, the name of the fort was also changed to Lalbagh Fort.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ticket price to enter the fort&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Children under the age of 5 do not need a ticket to enter Lalbagh Fort. Domestic visitors have to pay Rs 10 per person to enter the fort and Rs 100 per person for foreign tourists.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;br&gt;How to get to Lalbagh Fort&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;From Gulistan Golap Shah\'s shrine, you can go to Lalbagh fort with only 6 rupees. There is a special bus service to visit Lalbagh Fort from the front of Bangladesh National Museum located in Shahbag. Besides, you can easily reach Lalbagh Fort by renting a rickshaw from New Market and Gulistan in Dhaka for 40 to 50 rupees.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lalbagh Fort is closed for full and half days on Sundays and Mondays of the week respectively. Lalbagh fort is also closed on all special public holidays. The schedule of visiting Lalbagh fort changes from time to time.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schedule to visit Lalbagh Fort&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;April to September (summer)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sunday &lt;/strong&gt;- Weekly off&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monday&lt;/strong&gt; - 2:30 to 6 p.m.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Friday &lt;/strong&gt;- 10am to 6pm (closed between 12:30 pm and 2pm)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The rest of the week&lt;/strong&gt; - 10am to 6pm (sometimes closed from 1:00 pm to 1:30 pm)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;October to March (winter)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sunday &lt;/strong&gt;- Weekly off&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monday &lt;/strong&gt;- 2:30 pm to 5 pm&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Friday &lt;/strong&gt;- 9am to 5pm (sometimes closed from 12:30 pm to 2pm)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rest of the week &lt;/strong&gt;- 9am to 5pm (sometimes closed from 1:00 pm to 1:30 pm)&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-23 22:00:29'),
(19, 23, 9, 'Ahsan Manzil, Dhaka', '1624464968_ahsan-manzil-dhaka.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Ahsan Manzil&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ahsan Manzil is located on the banks of the river Buriganga in Islampur, Old Dhaka. The veranda and floor of the two-storey building are made of marble. Each room of Ahsan Manzil is octagonal and the roof of this building is made of wood. Inside the palace are the dining hall, library, pool, court hall and billiard play area. And on the second floor of the palace there are guest rooms, living room, dance hall, library and some other living rooms. Right in front of the palace is a beautiful flower garden and green field. A large staircase descends from the second floor of Ahsan Manzil to the green field.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Ticket price&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ordinary visitors have to collect an entrance ticket at Tk 20 per person to visit Ahsan Manzil. Children under the age of 12 can enter at 10 rupees per person. Foreigners have to pay 100 rupees per person to enter Ahsan Manzil. No tickets are required at Ahsan Manzil for disabled visitors. Students can also visit the Ahsan Manzil Museum for free if they apply in advance.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Proper time to visit&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ahsan Manzil is open to visitors from 10:30 am to 5:30 pm on these five days from Saturday to Wednesday. Ahsan Manzil can be visited every Friday from 3 pm to 8 pm. The Ahsan Manzil Museum is completely closed every Thursday and on other public holidays.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;How to go to Ahsan Manzil&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can come to Gulistan from anywhere in Dhaka and visit Ahsan Manzil by rickshaw or CNG. You will reach Islampur via Babubazar Bridge via Nayabazar Junction along North South Road of Gulistan. And Islampur is actually the way to Ahsan Manzil if you ask anyone you will know. Or you can come directly to the Sadarghat area of ​​old Dhaka and go to Ahsan Manzil on foot or by renting a rickshaw for a small fee.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-23 22:15:08'),
(20, 23, 9, 'Jahangirnagar University, Dhaka', '1624465835_Jahangirnagar-University-Dhaka-770x420.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Jahangirnagar University&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jahangirnagar University was established in 1960 in Savar upazila of Dhaka district in a captivating natural environment. The total area of ​​the university area is about 696.58 acres. It is well known as the only full-fledged residential university in Bangladesh. Butterfly Garden covers an area of ​​about 300 acres at Jahangirnagar University. There are about 110 species of butterflies in the flower garden to enjoy the beauty as well as learn about them. Through natural and artificial breeding in this garden more and more new butterflies are produced and released into the garden.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In winter, the guest bird fair is held on the lake of Jahangirnagar University campus covered with greenery. Guest birds include khanjana, sarali, patitara, patarihans, gyar, nonajotsa, lalmuri, dhupani, sindhu eagle, bamuniya duck, hood hood, barighora etc. The chirping of the guest birds, the jalkeli and the beauty of the red shuffler splashing in the water of the lake spread the fragrance of a unique natural beauty throughout the campus. As a result, this university became a gathering place for bird lovers as soon as winter came.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jahangirnagar University has about 16 lakes, big and small. However, Jahanara Imam and Pritilata Hall, the administrative building and the lake adjacent to Mir Mosharraf Hossain Hall have the highest number of guest birds. So the university administration has already declared the lakes as guest bird sanctuaries. These guest birds come to Bangladesh mainly from India, Nepal, Mongolia, Siberia and Xinjiang. They stay at Jahangirnagar University from late October to March.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;How to go&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The distance from the heart of the capital to Jahangirnagar University is only 32 kilometers. From Kalyanpur, Gulistan, Farmgate and Gabtali bus terminals in the capital Dhaka, you can take any bus going to Nabinagar or Manikganj and come directly in front of Jahangirnagar University campus. And you can choose rickshaw as a medium to visit the whole university.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-23 22:28:38'),
(21, 23, 9, 'Curzon Hall, Dhaka', '1624466420_Curzon-Hall-Dhaka-770x420.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Curzon Hall&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Curzon Hall is a 115-year-old historical building and antiquities located in the Dhaka University area. Curzon Hall is currently being used to teach science and biology molecules at Dhaka University. The foundation stone of the building was laid by the then Governor General George Curzon on February 14, 1904. From the repeal of the Partition of Bengal until the establishment of Dhaka University in 1921, Curzon Hall was used as a Dhaka College building.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Built in a unique blend of European and Mughal architectural styles, this two-storey Curzon Hall building is considered to be one of the architectural monuments of Dhaka. Inside the red-painted building is a huge central hall. There is a beautiful garden in front of Curzon Hall. A nice road runs from west to east through the garden. At the back of the building is the 400-year-old traditional Musa Khan Mosque, a huge pond and the main residential building of Sher-e-Bangla Fazlul Haq Hall. On the other side of the street opposite Curzon Hall are the Children\'s Academy and the traditional Doyle Square.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Curzon Hall has a lot of historical significance, not just as a witness to the times. After the partition of Bengal in 1905, Curzon Hall was used as the office of the provincial capital. It was from the historic Curzon Hall that the first public protest against making Urdu the sole state language took place.\r\n\r\nCurzon Hall can be visited at any time and there is no fee to visit Curzon Hall&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;How to get to Curzon Hall\r\n&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can visit this Curzon Hall of Dhaka University from anywhere in the capital Dhaka. And if you have your own car, there is no question. Or come to Shahbag by bus, from there you can rent a rickshaw for 15 to 20 rupees and go to Curzon Hall.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Where to eat\r\n&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Old Dhaka has a special tradition for food. Undoubtedly you can choose food items from Al Razzaq, Hajir Biryani, Kashmir Kachchi, Beauty Boarding or Sultan\'s Tea.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Everything else you see around Dhaka University\r\n&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you have time, you can spend an afternoon at Rose Garden, Ahsan Manzil, Shaheed Minar, Medical College, Doel Chattar, Sarwardi Udyan, Fine Arts Institute, National Museum or TSC.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-23 22:40:20'),
(22, 23, 10, 'Sajek Valley, Rangamati', '1624471052_Sajek-Resort-Cottage-770x420.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;Sajek Valley is currently the most popular destination for travel thirsty people. Sajek, located in Baghaichhari upazila of Rangamati district, is known as the largest union in Bangladesh. 1800 feet above sea level. Although Sajek is located in Rangamati district, it is very easy to travel to Sajek from Dighinala in Khagrachari due to geographical reasons. The distance from Khagrachhari district to Sajek is 60 km and from Dighinala is 40 km.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Beautiful mountain ranges all around, a valley of clouds like white cotton will fascinate you. Sajak is such an amazing place where on the same day you can be amazed by the presence of three different forms of nature. Sometimes it will feel very hot then maybe you will suddenly get wet in the rain or in the blink of an eye you will be surrounded by a thick mist of clouds. Sajek is an ideal place to watch the natural cosmos and the game of flying from the mountains to the clouds like cotton.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kanlak hill is the main attraction for tourists visiting Sajak. The last village in the Sajak Valley, Kanlak Para, is inhabited by the Lusai people. The origin of the river Karnafuli can be seen from Kanlak Para in the Lusai hills of India. If you want, you can trek for two hours from Ruilui Para to see Kamalak Jharna. This beautiful waterfall is also known as Pidam Taisa Jharna or Sikam Taisa Jharna to many.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can look around and see the tribal life. You will like the proximity of all these simple people. And if you have time, you can come back from Sajek Valley on the way back from Hajachhara Jharna, Dighinala Hanging Bridge and Dighinala Banavihar.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;When to go&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sajak\'s form is not really comparable. Sajek is dressed in colorful outfits throughout the year. You can visit Sajak at any time of the year. However, from July to November, clouds play more around Sajek. So this is the best time to visit Sajak.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Way to go to Sajek&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Although Sajek is located in Rangamati district, it is very easy to travel to Sajek via Dighinala in Khagrachhari district. So first you have to come to Khagrachhari. If you want to go to Khagrachhari from Dhaka, you can take Saudia, Shyamli, Shanti Paribahan, S Alam, Eagle etc. by bus. Non AC bus fare is 520 rupees. If you want to go by AC bus, you can go by BRTC and St. Martin transport for 600 rupeesThe buses usually leave for Khagrachhari by 10 pm. Besides, Shanti Paribahan bus goes directly to Dighinala, fare is 560 rupees. In Dhaka, there are counters of these transports in different parts of the city including Gabtali and Kalabagan. If you want to go on holidays, it is better to buy a ticket in advance or you may have trouble getting a ticket.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The distance from Khagrachhari to Sajek is about 60 kilometers. You can visit Sajek Valley from Shapla Chattar in Khagrachhari city with jeep / moon car reserve. The fare for two days including coming and going will be Rs 8,000-10,000. 12-15 people can go in one car. However, if there are less people, talking to another small group and sharing the car will cost less. If that is not possible then you can go to Sajek with CNG. Reserve rent will be 4000-5000 rupees. However, it is better not to travel by CNG as it is a hilly road.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel from Chittagong to Sajek&lt;/strong&gt;: You can go to Sajek from Chittagong via Khagrachhari or Dighinala. BRTC AC buses run 4 buses a day from Kadamtali in Chittagong at a fare of Tk. 200. Besides, Shanti Paribahan (fare Rs. 190) buses ply every hour from Oxygen Junction. It will take 4-5 hours to go to Khagrachhari by bus from Chittagong.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel from Rangamati to Sajek&lt;/strong&gt;: From Rangamati, Baghaichhari can be reached by both waterway and road. It takes 5-6 hours for the launch to leave the Reserve Bazaar launch dock between 8:30 am and 10:30 am every day. Rent per person is 150-250 rupees. The bus leaves from Rangamati bus terminal between 7.30 am and 8.30 am and charges Rs 200 per person. It takes 6-7 hours. It is also possible to go directly to Baghaichhari from Dhaka and Chittagong. From Baghaichhari you can reach Sajek Valley by jeep (Chader\'s car) or motorbike at a cost of Rs. 300 / - per person.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sajek Travel from Cox\'s Bazar&lt;/strong&gt;: Sajek can be reached from Cox\'s Bazar via Khagrachhari. Shanti Paribahan buses ply on Cox\'s Bazar-Khagrachhari route. The bus leaves Cox\'s Bazar at 9pm and 10pm for Khagrachhari. The fare for this non-AC bus is Tk 550.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are about a hundred resorts and cottages to stay in Saje. It will cost from Rs 1,500 to Rs 15,000 depending on the resort to get a room for one night. If you want to go on holiday, it is better to book a month in advance, otherwise there is less guarantee of getting a good room. And if you want to stay at a lower price, you can stay in the tribal cottages. In addition, many new cottages have been adapted to the environment. All the cottages in Sajek have a beautiful view.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Sajek resort and cottage&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resort RungRang: &lt;/strong&gt;Resort RungRang is one of the best resorts in Sajak. Sitting at the resort, it is ideal to see rows of mountains and clouds on the horizon. Decorated with aesthetic interior design, the resort has 4 double and 4 double rooms. On holidays double bed room rent is 3500 rupees and couple 2600 rupees. On all other days double bed room rent is 2600 rupees and couple 2000 rupees. Rungrang Resort Travel Guide offers 5-10% discount on room bookings for users. Tell the travel guide user as a reference at the time of booking and enjoy this special offer. Contact numbers for booking: 01884-710 723, 01869-649 817&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Runmoy Resort:&lt;/strong&gt; There are 5 rooms in total. Each room can accommodate 2 people. Downstairs room rent is 4450 rupees. Each room can accommodate 2 people. You can take an extra bed with 600 rupees. There are two rooms upstairs. The rent is 4950 rupees. Each room can accommodate two people. You can also get an extra bed with 800 rupees. Contact: 0186547688&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Megh Machang: &lt;/strong&gt;Many people prefer Megh Machang Resort for its beautiful view and relatively low cost. There are food and drink arrangements. Megh Machang has five cottages. Rent 3500-4500 rupees. Contact: 01822-168877&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jumghor Eco Resort&lt;/strong&gt;: This resort has a total of 6 couple rooms in separate cottages for accommodation. Each room has a maximum of 4 accommodations. The rent per cottage is 4000 rupees. Contact: 01884-208060&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sajek\'s food&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;All the resorts have food arrangements, so if you tell the resorts in advance, they will cook as per their choice. If you want you can do BQ at night. Besides, it can also be eaten at the tribal house. Don\'t miss the taste of papaya, pineapple, banana etc. very cheaply&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-23 23:57:32'),
(23, 23, 10, 'Keokradong, Bandarban', '1624549320_keokradong-770x420.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Keokradong&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Keokradong hill is located in Ruma upazila of Bandarban. At 3172 feet high, this mountain was once considered to be the highest mountain in Bangladesh but now it is the fifth highest mountain in modern terms. The name Keokradong comes from the local indigenous Marmas. Keokradong in Marma means the highest rocky mountain. From a distance, the peaks of Keokradang seem to be in the air. And when you reach the top, the combination of mountain clouds will move you with magical attraction&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Way to go to Keokdang&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Wherever you live in the country, you have to come to Bandarban first to go to Keokradong. S. from different places in Dhaka. Buses of Alam, Saudia, Saint Martin Transport, Unique, Hanif, Shyamli, Dolphin etc. leave for Bandarban. The fare of these buses per person is non AC 550 and AC 950-1500 respectively. It takes 8-10 hours to go to Bandarban by bus from Dhaka&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you want to go by train from Dhaka to Chittagong Sonar Bangla, Subarna Express, Turna Nishita, Mahanagar Godhuli you can go to Chittagong by these trains. Rent varies from 350 to 1200 rupees. Besides, you can come to Chittagong directly by air from Dhaka. From Baddarhat in Chittagong two pubs named Pubali and Purbani left for Bandarban. These two buses cost 220 rupees per person. You can come to Bandarban by bus from Dhampara bus stand in Chittagong for 200-300 taka.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Way to go Keokradong from Bandarban&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you want to go to Keokradong from Bandarban city, first you have to go to Ruma Bazaar. Then from Ruma Bazaar to Bagalek to Keokradong. One day it will be a little difficult to reach Keokradong from Bandarban. Tourists usually visit Bagale on the first day from one night to Keokradong the next morning. Visiting Bagalek and staying there will make your Keokradong trip more enjoyable.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The distance from Bandarban to Ruma Bazar is 48 kilometers. You can go to Ruma Bazaar by local bus or moon car / jeep. If you want to go by bus, you have to go to Ruma bus stand in Bandarban. From there the bus leaves for Rumara after 1 hour. The rent is 120 rupees per person, it will take about 3 hours. If you go in a group way, you can go to Ruma Bazaar by jeep / moon car. One car can go 10-15. You have to rent a car from the jeep station of Bandarban city for 3000-4000 rupees. If you do it by jeep, it will take about 2 hours.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;When you reach Ruma Bazaar, you must first pick up a guide to go to Keokdang. Guides are mandatory. The guide association has a registered guide, so someone has to fix it. You will have to bear the cost of the guide\'s food. Before leaving, one has to get permission to go to Keokradong from Ruma Bazar Army Camp. The identity of all traveling members must be submitted in writing for permission. The guide will help you to do these things. And of course keep in mind that you are not allowed to go to Bagalek from Rumabazar after 4 pm. Buy your own necessities from Rumabazar. There are some indigenous shops on the way to Bagalek and Keokdang, but you may not find what you need there.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The distance from Rumabazar to Bagalek is 16 kilometers. After getting permission, you have to rent a Land Cruiser Jeep or Moon Car from Rumabazar. One car can carry 8-15 people. You can take the help of a guide in these tasks. Explaining to the guide what you need will usually arrange all of those things. The reserve fare of Land Cruiser from Ruma to Bagalek is 1800 rupees and the car rental of Moon is 2000 rupees. If you have a small number of members, if you find another group, you can talk to them and fix a car together. Or you can buy a ticket and go to the local car. From 8 a.m. to 4 p.m., the local moon car arrives every hour. Local fare up to Bagalek is 100 rupees per person. Arrive at Bagalek and report to the army camp there. If you leave Bagale that night very early the next morning, you will be able to reach the top of Keokradong on foot (trekking) for 3-4 hours. This whole road from Bagalek to Keokradong has to be walked. You have to cross quite a few steep hills. If you want, you can reach Ruma Bazar from Keokradong the next day and then Bandarban. Otherwise you have to get down from Keokradong on that day and come to Bagale and reach Bandarban through Ruma day and night. But it is best to stay at the top of Keokradong hill for one night. The opportunity to watch the sunset and sunrise from the fifth highest mountain in Bangladesh should not be missed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Hiring Guide in Keokradong&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Going and coming by car&lt;/strong&gt; - 1,000 Taka per day &lt;strong&gt;Going and coming by car&lt;/strong&gt; - 1,800 Taka for 2 days&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kamalabazar / Bagalek by car then walk to and from Keokradong&lt;/strong&gt; - 2,000 Taka for 2 days &lt;strong&gt;Kamalabazar / Bagalek by car then walk to and from Keokradong&lt;/strong&gt; - 3 days&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Accommodation and meals at Keokradong&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you want to spend the night in Keokradong, there are indigenous cottages near the top of Keokradong. You can talk in advance through the guide or you can go and talk there. There should be a few people in a one-room cottage. Rent 100-150 rupees per person. Eating arrangements have to be made in the tribal houses. Usually food packages of 100-200 rupees are available. Meals are prepared with rice, eggs, mashed potatoes and mountain chicken. For this you have to tell in advance what to eat and how many people will eat. If you want to eat on arrival, you can tell with the help of the guide while leaving.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Arrangements for accommodation and food in Bagalek&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;Indigenous people have some small cottages. You have to stay in one of those cottages. It will cost 100-200 rupees per person for the tribals to stay in these cottages in a completely natural environment. One room cottage can accommodate 5-6 people. In addition, separate cottages can be arranged for couples or women. If you have any preferences in advance, tell the guide when you go and he will fix the cottage. Or you can go and fix it. The food system is similar to that of Keokradong.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Keokkradong Travel Tips&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You need to use good grip shoes for trekking. The lower the weight of your backpack, the easier the trekking will be. There is no electricity in Bagaleke and Keokradong, even if you have a solar power system, you can take a power bank with you to charge your mobile. Keep adequate water with you during trekking. When the water runs out, fill the bottle in a jhiri. Take a few packets of saline or glucose with you. Not all mobile networks are available, Teletalk and Robi networks are available. Be careful when bathing the heron, there is a lot of depth. The life journey of indigenous people is not like that of plain people, do not do anything that disrespects them. The whole road from Bandarban to Bagalek is a hilly winding road, be careful while traveling. Permission must be obtained from Army Camp from Ruma Bazar, must be reported to Baglake Army Camp. The same is true of Keokradong Camp.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-24 21:40:02'),
(24, 23, 10, 'Saint Martin, Cox\'s Bazar', '1624550706_Saint-Martins-Island-770x420.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Saint Martin&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;St. Martin St. Martin is the only coral island in Bangladesh, located in the southernmost part of the mainland. St. Martin is a small island of 16 sq km, 120 km from the district town of Cox\'s Bazar. St. Martin is also called Coconut Ginger in the local language. The island is one of the most beautiful tourist destinations in Bangladesh. The combination of the blue water of the sea with the infinite blue sky, the rows and rows of coconut trees have made this island unique, which attracts the people who are thirsty for travel. How to go Most of the ships to St. Martin leave Teknaf. So if you want to go to St. Martin, it is convenient to go to Teknaf in Cox\'s Bazar district. St. Martin can be reached by ship or trawler from Teknaf. If you want to go from Dhaka, it is convenient to go directly to Teknaf by bus and from there to St. Martin by ship / trawler. If you are planning to travel to Cox\'s Bazar, you can go from Dhaka to Cox\'s Bazar and then from Teknaf to St. Martin. Or you can take the MV Karnafuli Express ship directly from Cox\'s Bazar to St. Martin. Below are all the possible ways to go to St. Martin&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Teknaf from Dhaka&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can go directly to Teknaf by bus from Dhaka. Buses from Dhaka\'s Fakirapul and Sayedabad to Shyamli, Saint Martin Paribahan, Eagle, S Alam, Modern Line, Green Line etc. go directly to Teknaf. The fare for this 10-12 hour journey is usually between 900 to 2000 rupees depending on the bus and class. If you just want to go to St. Martin, it is best to take a direct bus from Dhaka to Teknaf. The bus left between 8-10 pm and reached Teknaf at 8 am. Teknaf from Dhaka to Cox\'s Bazar You can come to Cox\'s Bazar first from Dhaka and then go to Teknaf from Cox\'s Bazar. Many buses from Dhaka to Green Line, Sohag, TR Travels, Shyamoli, Hanif, Saudia, Eagle, S Alam, Silk Line, St. Martin, etc. leave for Cox\'s Bazar every day. Cox\'s Bazar can also be reached directly by air from Dhaka.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Cox\'s Bazar to Teknaf:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Local bus / micro / jeep / CNG can be rented from Cox\'s Bazar to Teknaf. The bus fare from Cox\'s Bazar to Teknaf is Tk 150 and CNG fare is Tk 250 per person. Depending on the situation, it takes about two hours to reach Teknaf. If you want to catch a ship in the morning, you have to leave Cox\'s Bazar for Teknaf in the morning (by 6 am). Teknaf from Ttgram S Alam and Saudia buses left Cinema Palace in Chittagong for Teknaf at 12 midnight. Besides, some buses from GSE Garibullah Shah Mazar and Dampara also run on Chittagong-Teknaf route.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;St. Martin from Teknaf&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ships like Kerry Sindabad, Kerry Cruise, MV Farhan, Atlantic etc. come and go from Teknaf to St. Martin every morning till November-March. It takes two hours to two and a half hours to travel from Teknaf to St. Martin by ship. Ticket fare to and from the ship is Tk. 650-1500. Ships depart daily from the jetty for St. Martin at 9.00-9.30 am and return from St. Martin at 3.00-3.30 pm. Therefore, failure to arrive at the jetty ahead of time increases the chances of missing the ship. And in such cases there is no way but to return to the trawler which is very dangerous. Ship tickets to St.Martin usually come and go. You need to specify when to return the ticket. From November 1, 2020, the Teknaf-Saint Martin sea route will be launched. The ship usually runs for five months from November to March / April. If you go to a time other than this time, you have to go by trawler or speedboat. The rest of the time, except the winter season, the sea is rough, so travel is not safe at this time. Trackers, speedboats and freight trawlers leave from Teknaf Namarbazar Bridge or Jetty Ghat. During the season, ships leave the wharf and trawlers leave. Usually trawlers and cargo boats cost 150-250 taka. It varies from season to season. It takes about 3 hours. For more information on which ships sail to St. Maarten, how much is the ticket price, where to book a ticket and how to get in touch, read: How to get to St. Martin from Teknaf.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;What to eat and where to eat&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The most famous thing in St. Martin is the dab which is both sweet and delicious. At least one dab test should be done when going to St. Martin. For those who like to eat fish, St. Martin\'s Coral, Sundari Poya, Hilsa, Rupchanda, Lobster, Kalachanda etc. are waiting with different types and flavors. All the hotels have the opportunity to buy barbecue by choosing fish as you like. Resorts also have their own barbecue arrangements. And if you have the opportunity, you can try kura (desi chicken is called kura). There are also endless stocks of dried fish known as Laita, Churi, Rupchanda, Kachki etc. Also some of the hotels and restaurants you can visit are Kerry Marjan Restaurant, Beach Point, Hotel Allar Dan, Bazar Beach, Assam Hotel, Sea Beach, St. Martin\'s, Comilla Restaurant, Real Restaurant, Haji Selim Park, St. Martin\'s Tourist Park etc. . However, you must check a little.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Where to stay&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;St. Martin has several well-appointed hotels and cottages for overnight stays. Many homes also have accommodation facilities for tourists.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blue Marine Resort&lt;/strong&gt;: The Blue Marine Resort is located very close to the ferry terminal on St. Martin\'s Island. The rent for an AC-equipped double bedroom at Blue-Marine Resort is Tk. 15,000 and non-AC Tk. 5,000, the rent for each triple red room is Tk. 3,000, the rent for a six-person bedroom is Tk. 4,000 and the rent for a ten-person bedroom is Tk. 5,000. Contact: 01817 060065&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Praasad Paradise Resort:&lt;/strong&gt; A lovely palace paradise as you cross the Blue Marine Resort through St. Martin\'s Market and head further north. Renting any one of the 16 different types of rooms will cost 2000-5000 taka. Contact: 01995 539248, 01883 626003&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Neel Digante Resort&lt;/strong&gt;: Located on the corner of South Beach on St. Martin\'s Island, Neel Digante Resort is a short distance from the jetty. It will cost 1500-5000 taka to stay in various types of cottage type rooms of the resort on the blue horizon. Contact: 0173 005 1004&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prince Heaven Resort:&lt;/strong&gt; Adjacent to the Palace Paradise on North Beach, Prince Haven Resort has a total of 24 rooms and a restaurant. Room rent at Prince Haven Resort is Tk. 1,500-3,500. Contact: 01995 539 246, 01883 626 002&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;What to do and what to see&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Those who come back from St. Martin day by day may regret it later so it is best to stay in St. Martin for at least one day. This delightful trip will always fascinate you as you can see the whole island.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Day Long Trip:&lt;/strong&gt; For those who want to travel to St. Martin on a day long trip due to lack of time, take a van and go straight to West Beach or Main Beach without wasting time. For this you have to calculate the van rent of 150 to 200 rupees. It takes 20 to 25 minutes to walk here, but it would not be right to waste time on a day long trip. This place is good for getting into the water so if you want to come to the beach you can soak your body in clear water. Whatever you do, keep in mind that you have to be free before 2 o\'clock or you won\'t even get time to eat. And of course you have to get on the ship before 3 o\'clock. If you have time, you can visit Humayun Ahmed\'s cottage near Main Beach. This type of trip to St. Martin will limit your time so come to St. Martin with a plan of at least one day.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 day plan:&lt;/strong&gt; Those who come to St. Martin with a one day plan should get off the ship and go to the hotel. After lunch you can come back to Chhera Island with a light rest. Try to leave before 4 o\'clock, then you can return to Chhera Island after watching the sunset. The sunset on Chhera Island is awesome but don&rsquo;t be too late after sunset. In the evening you can return to the main island to hang out at the market jetty or sit anywhere on West Beach. You can do bar-b-que at the resort at night. Although the price of fish at the resort is a little higher, the fish stays fresh. Or you can barbecue and eat fish of your choice at a nearby hotel. Spend the next morning walking around or come back from Chhera Island in the morning if you haven\'t been to Chhera Island the day before. Come back before noon, take a bath, have lunch and slowly get on the scheduled ship by 2:30.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Travel costs to St.Martin&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel cost&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bus ticket - Tk. 1,800 (non AC), Tk. 3,100-3,400 (AC) including round trip.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ship / Ship Rent - Tk. 600-700 (Open Deck), Tk.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Chhera Island - 200 Tk for boat.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Local Travel - Van fare to St. Martin\'s Market or nearby is 150-200 Tk.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Other expenses - Rs.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The cost of food&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Day of departure - 100-200 Tk for dinner at journey break.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Day 1 - Breakfast 80-100 Tk, lunch 120-220 Tk and dinner / bar BQ 200-300 Tk.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Day 2 - Breakfast 80-100 Tk, lunch 120-220 Tk. Day of return - 100-200 Tk for dinner on departure break&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The cost of accommodation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Standard hotel / resort couple room or double bed 1500-2500 Tk. Towards the market, the average quality hotel is 800-1200 Tk. Rents will increase a little more during the peak season and public holidays. Having a few people in one room will reduce the cost by sharing. The cost will be less if you go without peak season and holidays. Besides, if you want to stay at a lower cost, you can stay at home with less money for the local people, for this you have to find and talk a little.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-24 22:05:06'),
(25, 23, 11, 'Ratargul Swamp Forest, Sylhet', '1624554231_ratargul-swamp-forest-1.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Ratargul Swamp Forest&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ratargul is the only swamp forest in Bangladesh. It is located in Gowainghat upazila, about 26 km from Sylhet district town. The Ratargul forest covers an area of ​​about 30,325 acres. This vast area consists of 504 acres of forest and the rest is filled with small and large water bodies. However, in the rainy season, the whole area looks the same. Ratargul is known as the \'Sundarbans of Sylhet\'. Ratargul wetlands are submerged for four to five months in a year. Then tourists from different parts of Bangladesh came to see the submerged forest trees. Many tourists refer to Ratargul as the \'Amazon of Bangladesh\'. In the rainy season, various species of birds can be seen on the branches of trees, and then some wild animals also take shelter in the branches of trees. Besides, in winter, thousands of guest birds sit on the Ratargul pond. The best time to visit Ratargul is usually from July to October (late monsoon). Ratargul is a natural forest, the local forest department planted several trees here including Hijal, Varun, Karach. There are also about 25 species of water tolerant plants including Kadam, Jalibet, Arjuna. In 1983, the Bangladesh Forest Department declared 504 acres of Ratargul forest as a wildlife sanctuary.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&amp;nbsp;Way to go Ratargul&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sylhet-bound buses leave from Gabtoli, Fakirapul and Sayedabad bus terminals in Dhaka. Tickets for AC buses of Green Line, Saudia, S Alam, Shyamli, ENA etc. cost Tk.1000 to Tk. 1200 per bus. And the ticket price for non-AC bus is 480 to 600 rupees per person. You can choose to travel from Dhaka to Sylhet by train from Kamalapur or Airport Railway Station to Upban, Jayantika, Parabat or Kalni Express as your travel companion. You can also go to Sylhet by train from Chittagong, two trains called Paharika and Udayan Express run 6 days a week. You can choose the sky route to go from Dhaka in the fastest time and in comfort. Biman Bangladesh, Regent Air, United Air, Novo Air and US Bangla Air operate Dhaka-Sylhet flights from Shahjalal International Airport.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Way to go to Ratargul from Sylhet&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ratargul can be reached from Sylhet in two ways. Ratargul can be reached in a very short time by the road inside Khadim Tea Garden and Khadimnagar National Park near Sylhet city. This way you have to go to Sringi Bridge by CNG autorickshaw or jeep. From Sylhet you can go to Ratargul in the morning and come back in the afternoon. So it will cost 1200 to 1500 Tk. for CNG or autorickshaw for the whole day. If you rent CNG all day, you can also return to Bichnakandi at almost the same fare. If you want to take local CNG from Amberkhana in Sylhet, it will cost 100 rupees per person to reach Sringi Bridge. To reserve CNG, you must go to Damadami. From Sringi Bridge you will find small fishing boats to enter the Ratargul forest. A small boat can carry 4-5 people. The rent of such a boat is 750 Tk. Life jackets, umbrellas and midget hats are available for rent at night. On the second way to Ratargul, you have to take a car from Sylhet to Jaflong and get off at Sarighat. Local fare from Sylhet to Sarighat is 40 to 50 Tk. From Sarighat you have to come to Gowainghat market by CNG and go to Ratargul by boat. However, this route takes more time. Apart from this, you can reach Matarghat via Saheb Bazar from Bandar Bazar Point in Sylhet via CNG and rent a dinghy boat to go to Ratargul Jalaban It is important to remember that no matter which way Ratargul comes from, fishermen will have to rent a small boat to enter the forest. A boat can seat a maximum of 4-5 people&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Where to stay&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are many quality residential hotels and rest houses in Lala Bazar area and Dargah Road at low rents. Where you will get different types of rooms for 500 to 1000 Tk. Besides, you can stay in Hotel Hill Town, Gulshan, Dargah Gate, Surma, Kaikobad etc. according to your need and ability. Good service residential hotels include Hotel Holy Gate, Holy Inn, La Vista Hotel, Pansy Inn, Hotel Metro International, Britannia Hotel, etc. The cost of staying in these hotels will be from Tk. 2,000 to Tk. 10,000. Luxury hotels and resorts include Nirvana Inn, Hotel Nurjahan Grand, Rose View Hotel, Nazimgar Resort, Grand Palace and some more. The cost per night will range from Tk. 8,000 to Tk. 30,000.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Caution when traveling Ratargul&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Snakes usually take shelter in the branches of different trees after the forest is submerged in the rainy season, be careful about this. There are also leech infestations here. If you do not know how to swim, keep a life jacket with you. If necessary, take an umbrella and a raincoat&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-24 23:03:51'),
(26, 23, 16, 'Birishiri, Netrokona', '1624555264_birishiri-netrokona-770x420.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Birishiri&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Birishiri is a traditional village in Durgapur upazila of Netrokona district. Vijaypur in Birishiri has attractive porcelain hills and blue water lakes. These porcelain hills and plains of Vijaypur are about 16 km long and 600 m wide. The blue water of the lake instantly removes all fatigue and exhaustion. The main source of the blue water of the lake is the Sameshwari river. This river is now better known as coal mine. Like the lake of blue fire, the river Someshwari is unique in its own way.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Everything else you will see in Birishiri&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The porcelain hills in Birishiri, the blue water lake are also ideal places to visit Someshwari River, Ranikhong Church and Kamala Rani Dighi. The beauty of Kashaban and distant Garo hills on the banks of Someshwari river fascinates all the travelers who come to Birishiri. During the monsoon season, the Someshwari River is in full swing, and tourists flock to see the beauty of Birishiri\'s youth. There are also hill cultural academies, Garo, Hajong etc. ethnic groups, several monuments of the Tungka Revolution or Tebhaga movement in the Hajong language and St. Joseph\'s Church.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Way to go to Birishiri&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Government and Jinnat Paribahan buses leave for Durgapur directly from Dhaka\'s Mohakhali bus terminal. It takes 250 to 350 Tk to go to Durgapur by these two buses. Although called Durgapur, these buses usually go to Sukhnagari. From Sukhnagari you have to cross a small river by boat and go to Durgapur by rickshaw, bus or motorbike. You can go to Durgapur by going for 20 rupees by bus, 80 to 100 Tk by rickshaw and 100 rupees by motorbike. From Dhaka at 11:50 pm you can take the Haor Express train to Shyamganj train station and from there you can take a bus or CNG fare to Birishiri Bazar. Or if you want to go a little easier, you can come to Netrokona by Haor Express train and return from Challisha Bazar on a motorbike for 300 Tk per person to see all the spots. Apart from this, one can reach Durgapur by taking a train from the airport railway station at 4.00 / 4.30 am to Jaria station for 80 to 100 rupees and by trawler, auto, CNG or motorbike. From Chittagong\'s Alangkar Mor, some standard buses leave for Birishiri. These buses cost 450 to 600 Tk. Battery powered rickshaws can be rented from Birishiri Bazaar for Rs 500 to Tk 600 and you can see all the places in 5-6 hours. On the way back to Dhaka from Durgapur, two night coaches left for Mohakhali in Dhaka at 11:30 pm and 11:30 am from in front of Talukdar Plaza in Durgapur. Besides, a train from Zaria train station left for Dhaka at 12 noon.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Where to stay Susang&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Durgapur has Zilla Parishad Dak Bungalows, several guest houses and medium quality residential hotels for overnight stays. If necessary, you can contact - District Council Postal Bungalow (01558380383, 01725571795), Youth Men Christian Association or YMCA Rest House (01818613496, 01716277637, 01714418039, 01743306230, 019). -Gosthi Cultural Academy Guest House (09525-56042, 01815482006) Notable among the medium quality hotels in Durgapur are - Swarna Guest House (0171228698, 01728438712), Hotel Susang (01914791254), Hotel Gulshan (01711150807), Hotel Jaba (01711186708, 01753154617), Nadi. These hotels offer overnight stays at Tk 200 to Tk 500.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Where to eat&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can keep it with light food while visiting Birishiri as there is not much food available everywhere. There are some medium quality food hotels or restaurants where rice, pulses, fish, meat as well as buck meat are available. Don\'t forget to taste the famous pillow sweets of Netrokona in Durgapur Bazaar.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-24 23:21:04'),
(27, 23, 15, 'Tazhat Palace, Rangpur', '1624556548_tazhatpalace.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Tajhat zamindar house&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;To see the Tajhat Zamindar Bari (Tajhat Palace) you have to go to the village of Tajhat in Mahiganj, about 8 km from the Rangpur divisional town. In the late eighteenth century, the gem trader Mannalal came to Mahiganj for business and later became the founder of the Tajhat zamindari. After the death of zamindar Mannalal, his adopted son Gopal Lal Roy Bahadur started managing the zamindari. At the beginning of the twentieth century, the present Tajhat zamindar house was completed with the relentless work of about 2000 masons. The construction of this zamindar house, which was completed in 1917, cost about Rs 1.5 crore at that time.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are rows of trees in the courtyard of the Tajhat zamindar\'s house, a huge field and two ponds on either side of the palace. And there are different kinds of flowers and mahogany, kamini, mango and jackfruit gardens. The zamindar house looks like Ahsan Manzil in Dhaka. On the third and fourth floors of the four-storied Tajhat zamindar house made of red brick, white and limestone are various items used by zamindar Gopal. There are also living rooms, bathrooms and guest rooms. The Tajhat zamindar\'s house, built in imitation of ancient Mughal architecture, is about 210 feet wide and has 31 steps made of Italian marble. At the back of the palace is the secret stairway, which is now closed. In 1995, the Bangladesh Archaeological Department registered the Tajhat Zamindar Bari as a protected structure and in 2005 relocated the Rangpur Museum to the second floor of the Tajhat Zamindar Bari. The museum\'s exhibition hall houses a number of terracotta works of the tenth and eleventh centuries. The museum also preserves ancient manuscripts in Arabic and Sanskrit, including the Qur\'an, the Mahabharata and the Ramayana of the Mughal emperor Aurangzeb. In addition to the black stone portrait of Vishnu, the museum has about 300 valuable artefacts.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Schedule to visit Tajhat Zamindar Bari and Rangpur Museum&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;During the summer months, i.e. from April to September, the Rangpur Museum or Tajhat Zamindar Bari is open from 10 am to 6 pm. In winter, i.e. from October to March, it is open for inspection from 9 am to 5 pm. The Rangpur Museum is closed for lunch from 1pm to 1:30 pm. The museum is closed for half a day on Mondays, full Sundays every week of the week. Visits to the museum are also closed on all public holidays&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Ticket price for Tajhat Zamindar Bari and Rangpur Museum&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;All adult Bangladeshi citizens have to pay 20 rupees to enter the Rangpur Museum. Secondary level students have to collect a ticket for 5 rupees to enter the Tajhat zamindar\'s house, but children under 5 do not need a ticket to enter. In addition, the entrance ticket for visitors from SAARC countries costs 100 rupees and the entrance ticket for any other foreigner costs 200 rupees.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;How to go&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;From the Kalyanpur, Gabtali and Mohakhali bus terminals of the capital Dhaka, buses of various modes regularly travel to Rangpur. These buses cost 800 to 1000 rupees per person to go to Rangpur. It costs only 20 rupees to go to Tajhat zamindar\'s house by rickshaw from Rangpur bus stand. However, if you take a bus from Dhaka to Kurigram, you can get off directly in front of the Tajhat zamindar\'s house.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If necessary you can contact: Greenline Transportation: 88-02-9112287, 88-02-9133145, 01730060006 Alhamara Travels: 88-02-9005612, 01721802031 Meem Transport - 01911-013694, 01734422971 SR Travels: Kalyanpur - 01711394801, 88-02-9033793, Gabtali - 88-02-9031226, Mohakhali - 01552-315831, Uttara - 01711-394804 Kurigram Transport 01924469437, 01914856826&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Where to stay in Rangpur&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are several hotels / motels of different quality to stay in Rangpur city. With a little research you can easily spend the night in the hotel of your choice. Among the notable hotels in Rangpur&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hotel Northview: 0521-55405, 0521-55406,&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tourist Motel: 0521-62111&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Park Hotel: 0521-65920&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hotel Golden Tower: 0521-65920&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hotel Tilottama: 0521-63482, 01718938424,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hotel Kashpia: 0521-61111, 01977-227742&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Where to eat&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;In the divisional city of Rangpur, you can get your fill from various quality hotels / restaurants, but if you go to Rangpur during the mango season, don\'t forget to eat the famous Haribhanga Mango of Rangpur.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-24 23:42:28');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `user_id`, `topic_id`, `title`, `image`, `body`, `published`, `created_at`) VALUES
(28, 23, 14, 'Kuakata Beach, Patuakhali', '1624561135_kuakata.jpg', '&lt;h2&gt;Kuakata Beach&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kuakata beach is located in Latachapali union of Kalapara police station in Patuakhali district. Sunrise and sunset can be seen at the same time from this 18 km long Kuakata beach. This feature makes Kuakata unique from all the beaches. The sunrise is best seen from the Gangamati bend on the eastern side of the beach. And the best place to watch the sunset is the west beach of Kuakata. There is a huge sea on one side of the beach and rows of coconut trees on the other side. Kuakata\'s clean beaches, impeccably beautiful beaches, horizontal blue skies and mangrove forests add a different dimension to Kuakata.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Fishermen can be seen fishing on Kuakata beach almost all year round. If you want to go to the beach, you can rent a motorcycle and a horse. The amount of rental money usually depends on the distance and time. There are also several chars near Kuakata. Speedboats, trawlers, and large motor boats are available. There is also a picnic near Kuakata beach.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Sights of Kuakata&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shuntki Palli:&lt;/strong&gt; Jale Palli is located at the western end of Kuakata beach. The dry season lasts from November to March. The fish is caught from the sea and dried on the beach. If you want, you can spend time watching this busyness of fishermen. And you can buy different types of dried fruits at low prices.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crab Island&lt;/strong&gt;: A long way east along Kuakata Beach, Crab Island or Crab Island is a popular spot. Thousands of red crabs roam the secluded beach. During the travel season, from October to March, speed boats from Kuakat Beach to Crab Island are available.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jungle of Gangamati:&lt;/strong&gt; Kuakata beach has come to an end up to Gangamati canal on the east side. And from this place the forest of Gangamati started. In addition to different species of plants, a variety of birds, forest roosters, monkeys, etc. can be seen in this forest. To many, this forest is known as the forest of Gajmati.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fatra Forest:&lt;/strong&gt; The Fatra Forest starts from the other side of the river on the west side of the beach. This forest has almost all the features of Sundarbans. Forest roosters, monkeys, wild pigs and various birds are found here. If you want to go from Kuakata to Fatra forest, you have to rent an engine boat.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kuakata Well:&lt;/strong&gt; The well that bears witness to the history behind the naming of Kuakata is still there. If you want to see this well, you have to go to Keranipara, the residence of Rakhine. As soon as you enter this place, you will see the ancient well. It is said that after being expelled from the motherland in 184, the Rakhine took refuge on the island of Rangabali on the shores of the Bay of Bengal. As the salt water of the sea was unsuitable for use, they dug wells for fresh water and the place gradually became known as Kuakata.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Seema Buddhist Temple:&lt;/strong&gt; Seema Buddhist Temple is located just in front of the ancient well of Kuakata. The wooden temple was demolished a few years ago. The temple contains an ancient Buddhist statue of octahedron weighing about 36 manas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keranipara&lt;/strong&gt;: Keranipara, the abode of the Rakhine, is just a short walk along the road to Seema Buddhist Temple. Rakhine women are very skilled in weaving cloth and the winter sheets they make are very attractive.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Misripara&lt;/strong&gt; Buddhist Temple: There is a large Buddhist temple at Misripara, another Rakhine village, about eight kilometers from Kuakata beach. It is rumored that the temple has the largest Buddhist statue in the subcontinent&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;How to go&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Kuakata can be reached from Dhaka by river and road. Launch from Dhaka Sadarghat via Patuakhali or Barisal to Kuakata. And if you want to go by bus from Dhaka to Barisal via Kuakata. However, considering the easiest and most comfortable way, the river is the best way to go to Kuakata. From Dhaka\'s Sadarghat Launch Terminal you can take a launch to Patuakhali and from there you can take a bus to Kuakata. Or you can go to Barisal from Sadarghat by launch and go to Kuakata by bus from there.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Launch from Dhaka to Kuakata via Patuakhali:&lt;/strong&gt; After launch from Sadarghat in the afternoon Sundarban-9, Kuakata-1, MV Prince Awlad-6, Kajal-6, Sundarbans-11, MVAR Khan-1 etc. left for Patuakhali. In these launches, it costs Tk 800 to Tk 1,000 to rent a first class single cabin, Tk 1,800 to Tk 3,500 for a double cabin and Tk 200-300 for a deck. The launches go to different terminals in Patuakhali. It is convenient to go to the launch that goes to Amtali Ghat or Patuakhali Launch Ghat. From Patuakhali launch ghat you have to go to the bus stand by auto and go to Kuakata by bus. It will take about 2 hours, the rent is 130-150 Tk. Or you can get off at Amtali Ghat and go to Kuakata from the bus stand for 50-60 Tk.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Launch from Dhaka to Barisal via Kuakata: &lt;/strong&gt;More than one launch left Sadarghat for Barisal in the evening. He reached Barisal in the morning. Launch deck rent is 150-200 Tk per person. The launch costs from Rs 600 to Tk 3,500 depending on the first class single and double cabin class. From Barshal Launch Ghat, you have to go to Rupatali Bus Stand and get on any bus going to Kuakata. It will take about 3 hours. Rent 180-250 Tk. Besides, you can go to Kuakata from Barisal without renting a car.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;By bus from Dhaka to Kuakata&lt;/strong&gt;: Kuakata can be reached by bus of Sakura Paribahan, Druti Paribahan, Survi Paribahan from Gabtoli bus stand in Dhaka. Non-AC bus fare is 650 to 600 Tk per person and AC bus fare is 1000 rupees. In addition, buses leave from Kamalapur BRTC bus depot for Kuakata every morning and night.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Where to stay in Kuakata&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;There are various quality residential hotels in Kuakata for tourists to stay. Depending on the standard and class, you can stay in these hotels for 400-5,000 rupTkees. Costs will be lower if a few people share together to reduce hotel room rent. There is no need to book a hotel in advance after the season and public holidays. And of course you will do it. Among the hotels in Kuakata:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Youth in Hotel:&lt;/strong&gt; Rooms of different quality can be rented at this hotel of Tourism Corporation for 1500 to 5000 Tk, Phone: 04428-56207.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Holiday Homes Hotel&lt;/strong&gt;: This hotel of the Tourism Corporation offers different rooms for 800 to 2000 Tk. Phone: 04428-56004&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;These two hotels of the Tourism Corporation can be booked from the Tourism Head Office in Dhaka. Contact: 02-8811109, 02-989288.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hotel Graver Inn:&lt;/strong&gt; Room rent is 3000-5000 Tk according to different standards of this hotel with some facilities. Contact: 01833-318380.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sea View Hotel:&lt;/strong&gt; Room rent is 800-2000 Tk.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Beach Haven Resort:&lt;/strong&gt; AC and non-AC single room rent 800-1000 Tk.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sea Gull&lt;/strong&gt;: Room rent is 1200-2000 Tk.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Among the hotels in Kuakata, Hotel Banani Palace, Hotel Kuakat Inn, Hotel Nilanjana, Hotel Golden Palace etc. are notable.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Food facilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hotels in Kuakata arrange their own meals for their guests in their own restaurants. Besides, a variety of local food is also available in the local restaurants here.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-06-25 00:58:55');

